Detailed Description

The section has a list of all internal data structures which are used internally by the module.

Typedef Documentation

typedef struct TestFmk_HWAttribute_t TestFmk_HWAttribute

Test Framework HW Attributes.

This the Test Framework SOC HW Attributes which will allow the module to be ported

typedef struct TestFmk_LocalIPCMsg_t TestFmk_LocalIPCMsg

Test Framework Local IPC Message.

The structure is used to exchange local IPC messages

typedef struct TestFmk_MCB_t TestFmk_MCB

Test Framework Master control block.

The structure is used to hold all the relevant information required to execute the Test Framework module

typedef enum TestFmk_MessageType_e TestFmk_MessageType

Enumeration for Test Framework IPC messages.

The Test Framework IPC module exchanges messages between the Test Framework Peers. The enumeration describes the different types of messages which can be exchanged.

typedef struct TestFmk_Msg_t TestFmk_Msg

Test Framework Message Format.

The structure describes the Test Framework message format

typedef struct TestFmk_ProfileMsg_t TestFmk_ProfileMsg

Test Framework Profile specific message.

The structure describes the profile message. Profile specific messages are not interpreted by the Test Framework module. These are simply transported as is to the profile. Interpretation of these messages is done by the profile.

typedef struct TestFmk_ResponseMsg_t TestFmk_ResponseMsg

Test Framework Response Format.

The structure describes the response. Responses are sent back to the peer which initiated the Test Framework IPC Request to indicate the status of the operation. Applications are notified though the reporting mechanism

Enumeration Type Documentation

enum TestFmk_MessageType_e

Enumeration for Test Framework IPC messages.

The Test Framework IPC module exchanges messages between the Test Framework Peers. The enumeration describes the different types of messages which can be exchanged.

Enumerator
TestFmk_MessageType_LOAD 

Message to indicate that the profile has been loaded.

TestFmk_MessageType_OPEN 

Message sent to indicate that the profile has been opened.

TestFmk_MessageType_CLOSE 

Message sent to indicate that the profile has been closed.

TestFmk_MessageType_START 

Message sent to indicate that the profile has been started.

TestFmk_MessageType_SET_TESTFMK_CFG 

Message sent to indicate that the profile has received the configuration.

TestFmk_MessageType_STOP 

Message sent to indicate that the profile has been stopped.

TestFmk_MessageType_UNLOAD 

Message sent to indicate that the profile has been unloaded.

TestFmk_MessageType_PROFILE 

Profile specific message. This is simply passed to the profile without interpretation.

TestFmk_MessageType_FAULT 

Message sent to indicate that there was a CPU/ESM Fault reported by the ESM Layer.

TestFmk_MessageType_RESPONSE 

Response message.
